From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Keyur Maru <kd2maru@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 05:10:06 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] motorola: build the overlay and lineage-HAL sepolicy without
 the LineageOS framework

This tree assumes a full LineageOS build; on plain AOSP-17 two of its
assumptions do not hold:

- overlay: the MotoEuicc phony pulls in EuiccPolicy, the LineageOS framework
  eSIM-policy app, which is not grafted here. Keep only the device-specific
  EuiccPolicyMoto RRO.
- sepolicy: the lineage-HAL sepolicy framework (the hal_attribute_lineage macro
  and the domain type declarations it emits) lives in LineageOS' system/sepolicy
  and is absent from AOSP's, so hal_lineage_touch_default and
  hal_lineage_powershare_default were never declared and recovery_sepolicy.cil
  failed to compile with "unknown type hal_lineage_touch_default". The rules in
  these files use the domain types directly rather than the lineage HAL
  attribute, so declaring the types (plus the touch service's exec_type and
  init_daemon_domain, exec label already set in this dir's file_contexts) is
  sufficient and stays neverallow-safe.
---
 overlay/Android.bp                                    |  3 ++-
 sepolicy/qti/vendor/hal_lineage_powershare_default.te |  5 +++++
 sepolicy/qti/vendor/hal_lineage_touch_default.te      | 11 +++++++++++
 3 files changed, 18 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/overlay/Android.bp b/overlay/Android.bp
index 81c890a..7b74c89 100644
--- a/overlay/Android.bp
+++ b/overlay/Android.bp
@@ -13,7 +13,8 @@ phony {
 phony {
     name: "MotoEuicc",
     required: [
-        "EuiccPolicy",
+        // EuiccPolicy is the LineageOS framework eSIM-policy app, not grafted
+        // into this AOSP tree. Keep only the device-specific Moto RRO.
         "EuiccPolicyMoto",
     ]
 }
diff --git a/sepolicy/qti/vendor/hal_lineage_powershare_default.te b/sepolicy/qti/vendor/hal_lineage_powershare_default.te
index ff811e9..60b7c3c 100644
--- a/sepolicy/qti/vendor/hal_lineage_powershare_default.te
+++ b/sepolicy/qti/vendor/hal_lineage_powershare_default.te
@@ -1,2 +1,7 @@
+# lineage-HAL framework not grafted into AOSP system/sepolicy; declare the
+# vendor.lineage.powershare service domain type (used directly by the rules below)
+# so recovery_sepolicy.cil compiles. Bare domain decl = neverallow-safe.
+type hal_lineage_powershare_default, domain;
+
 allow hal_lineage_powershare_default vendor_sysfs_usb_supply:dir r_dir_perms;
 allow hal_lineage_powershare_default vendor_sysfs_wlc:file rw_file_perms;
diff --git a/sepolicy/qti/vendor/hal_lineage_touch_default.te b/sepolicy/qti/vendor/hal_lineage_touch_default.te
index 0569fd6..31cd3ca 100644
--- a/sepolicy/qti/vendor/hal_lineage_touch_default.te
+++ b/sepolicy/qti/vendor/hal_lineage_touch_default.te
@@ -1 +1,12 @@
+# The lineage-HAL sepolicy framework (hal_attribute_lineage macro + these domain
+# type declarations) is not grafted into this AOSP system/sepolicy, so the
+# vendor.lineage.touch AIDL service domain types were undeclared -> recovery_sepolicy.cil
+# failed with "unknown type hal_lineage_touch_default". The allow rules here use the
+# domain types directly (not the hal_lineage_touch attribute), so declaring them as
+# domains/exec_type is sufficient and neverallow-safe. (Exec labeled on
+# /vendor/bin/hw/vendor.lineage.touch-service.motorola in this dir's file_contexts.)
+type hal_lineage_touch_default, domain;
+type hal_lineage_touch_default_exec, exec_type, vendor_file_type, file_type;
+init_daemon_domain(hal_lineage_touch_default)
+
 rw_dir_file(hal_lineage_touch_default, vendor_sysfs_touchpanel)
